reviews_data.review_text: Best blueberry donuts ever! A must try.
Lots of good baked items
Their donuts are so fresh and fluffy every time. They have great flavors and the staff are always super nice and friendly. Will continue to come back! Support a local business!
Sunday morning, about 10am, no one else there...friendly service, great selection. The apple fritter is very good.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Doughnut, Apple Fritter, Blueberry Glazed Donut

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome and amazing donuts! At first I thought they only had donuts which are out of this world amazing but then I also saw that they had all types of coffee and tea! Everything was wonderful! I got a coffee and a Vietnamese coffee there’s a lot of selections that are so good!!! We go to the Lamborghini events that get a bunch of these donuts and hand them out and I see why. Good customer service too, the lady’s were sweet! Overall my most favorite donuts in Charlotte!
Best donuts in Charlotte by far!!!
No idea because they're never opened when I attempt to go. Always "ran out of donuts" sign on the door.
Get donuts! They do sell out, sometimes around noon.
Went for the first time this morning. Bye 👋 Starbucks lol. I have found my spot.
The best donuts in the Charlotte metro area.  I love their apple fritter donuts. When you order a filled donut they fill it while you wait. Their donuts are always fresh and very soft.

We love the donuts, the different options for fillings and the apple fritters. Unfortunately, we are really disappointed to see that they are closing at 3 now. We love to stop by for an after school snack and if they close at 3 we can’t ever make it. Every time we would go in there we would run into other kids just getting out of school so I don’t know why they would choose to lose all that business. We will never be able to go anymore.
Cool

Awful service! I have purchased donuts from here before and they weren't bad like the service that I received but my family and I will NEVER spend any of our hard earned money here again and neither should you!

Saw this donut shop on our way to Great Wolf Lodge and I after Googling it I knew I had to stop on our way home. BOY OH BOY was it worth the stop. We went around 1pm but there was still a lot of variety of options left. These donuts were SOOOOOOO good! Trying to talk myself out of driving back to Charlotte to get some more!
Definitely a must have!
The BEST donuts!
Doughnuts are always fresh.
Best donuts in town. Donut holes are a must to snack on. Love this place. Amazing selection. Friendly service.  Delicious coffee. Cute inside with places to sit and eat.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Doughnut, Apple Fritter, Cake Donut, Maple Bacon, Buttermilk Cake Crumble Donut, Cinnamon Roll, Chocolate Glazed Donut with Sprinkles, Smores Doughnut Top Left, Blueberry Cake Donut, Cinnamon Sugar, Chocolate Coconut, Salted Caramel, Cinnamon Sugar Holes

reviews_data.review_text: My favorite thing to do in a city is to try their donuts. I checked a few and wasn’t impressed and then stumbled across Omg Donuts. There donuts were massive, colorful and delicious. My favorite feature was the select your own filling station ( Bavarian, white crème, raspberry and lemon). The staff was super friendly. I understand why they are rated so highly. I will definitely come back

This is a solid, all-around good place.   I had the lemon doughnut, and it was flavorful.  The service was friendly.   They warmed up the doughnut, which I believe made it so much better, and the place has a cute ambiance. It is tucked away a bit but appears to be a nice place to sit down and enjoy coffee in doughnuts, whether you're hanging out with family and friends,  on a date, or needing a quiet place to work and study as well.
These donuts are amazingly delicious. Me and the kids got a cinnamon roll, an apple fritter, and a frosted donut. I think they were the best I’ve ever had. Highly recommend if you were in the area.
Donuts are phenomenally fresh and they have amazing taste and texture. They remind me of my childhood donuts.  Absolutely, irresistible donuts!
Donuts where so soft and fluffy not to sweet they where pretty good, it would have been nice to have a little more variety, but again I have to say, they do what they do well.
Delicious…. Every time! OMG for the win!
One of the best chocolate long johns and cinnamon roll I have ever had. The staff were very friendly as well.
One of my favorites.
Loved the donuts, they are made fresh daily.
Drove from ohio.. been wanting these since I saw them 3 yrs ago.. gas 500 hotel 800 OMG DONUTS PRICELESS
Food. Service. Atmosphere. All 5/5!!! The donuts are perfectly fluffy, great size, and tasty flavors. Plus they are an amazing value for the price! My new go to spot!

Absolutely the best donut shop!!! Super friendly excellent customer service absolutely wonderful donuts and wonderful Vietnamese iced coffee. I have been to the shop many many times The donuts are consistently pillowy soft and the service is wonderful they're always happy to see you and happy to help and answer any questions you have. And I love that when I want a filled donut, I can choose my filling and they fill it right there on the spot everything is super fresh.
Absolutely delicious! Massive donuts, great selection. Two really kind ladies working. Will definitely return

A true disappointment!   I’ve seen a better selection at Dunkin Donuts.   The staff doesn’t even greet you when you walk in.   It was a no brainer to leave immediately.  I will not return.  OMG what a disappointment!

Other than some pretty good donuts, this is the most untrustworthy, and unreliable donut shop ever. Never open when they say they are with no signs or updates. The door at the front doesn’t even have their hours because they close and open whenever they feel like. This place is a guessing game and frankly, I’m not having fun. Highly suggest going somewhere else. There’s better donuts anyway.
The most amazing donuts in the area

Incredibly fresh and well-made donuts. Complex in flavor and great chew. You can pick your donut fillings, and there's even Bavarian cream! The people who work here are always a joy to talk to and I can't wait to go back.
First time coming here and it was amazing! donuts were so good and CHEAP! had to buy more! will for sure come back!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Apple Fritter, Cake Donut, Blueberry Glazed Donut

reviews_data.review_text: Best donut in town.  I have the maple bacon donut and maple bar quite often.  Very good.

The worst customer service I have ever experienced. The cashier couldn’t even initiate ordering or telling us what order was ours. It was the most bizarre experience like she couldn’t be bothered to do her job.
Great donuts, rating a 4 because they don’t have decaf coffee. Never been to a coffee shop that doesn’t have decaf.

We usually go to the Concord location but finally tried this location. The donuts were amazing as usual but I could’ve dealt without the young light skinned girls stale attitude that checked us out. She lacks all sense of any type of customer service. She felt very cold and uninviting. Other than that, the donuts are always great.
I enjoyed the treats I got here. I got some donut holes and a lemon filled and a creme filled donut. Looking forward to coming back

Read in entirety:
Just want to thank Krispy Kreme for no longer carrying blueberry cake donuts because it made me search for another donut shop. And as the clouds part and angels sing, we have found it!!  OMG Donuts !  The blueberry cake donut was very bluebery-eee and the lightest cake donut I have had.  But the best one (so far...) is their apple fritter donut.  It is THE BEST APPLE FRITTER DONUT EVER CREATED!
Now, on to try the creme filled donuts...(did you know you get to pick your filling and what kind of donut it goes into and they fill it right there?! I mean, COME ON!)

YES YES YES!!!... FRESH FRESH FRESH!!! The donuts are just so delicious, soft, and flavorful. You can tell they're fresh EVERYTIME. They even have different filling options that they fill right infront of you, FRESH!.
Take out order!

Just came from here, to pick up some donuts. Man, could the service be *anymore* underwhelming? One girl was handling the donuts, and another rang us up. Now SHE looked absolutely *thrilled* to be there. I could barely even hear what she said about how much I owed her because she barely moved her mouth. VERY lackluster, and could’ve cared less. And they have the audacity to ask for a tip??? That's hilarious. All around, it was a very awkward interaction. If I wanted service like that, I should've just gone to Dunkin or Krispy Kreme. They don't care either. Listen, if you guys want to stand out from the typical chains, hire people with a personality and TRAIN them on customer service!!! 3-stars for the donuts, but that's about it. It'll be a while before I go back. It’s enough to keep me away.
Best donuts for the price in Charlotte. $1.50-$2 for almost every donut while other places are charging 2x that! Give this place a visit, you will have a new fav donut spot too.

OMG is consistently delicious whenever we visit. I love the lemon doughnut and coffee and my husbands favorite is the Apple fritter. Actually, our entire family loves OMG as well. So much so we decided to have OMG at our wedding.  Our guests kept commenting how delicious everything was.

Highly recommend OMG for daily treats and large orders for events!

(Wedding Photography by: Jamie Marie Photography)
Came for coffee and left with an apple fritter and filled to order eclair (for wife). Wow. Best donuts I ever had. So fresh and crisp. Coffee was great too.
I don’t ever review anything but these are the best donuts in Charlotte hands down…
The best donuts I ever had!
Best donuts, hands down. A great selection and the apple fritters are a must have!!!
Best glazed yeast donuts. Ever.
Everyone was quick and friendly, donuts tasted great.

Love this place!  My kids and I wanted to surprise their Mom on Mother’s Day, as she is a NICU nurse & had to work. She & her co- workers loved the dozen doughnuts we brought in. The staff were super helpful/kind picking out her favorite doughnuts/chatting with me & the price was much cheaper than I thought it would be. My kids loved the doughnuts they picked for themselves & the restaurant itself was set up very nicely. Go OMG!

The coffee was good but the customer service was terrible. Both employees were very rude when I politely asked them to remake my coffee because they added sweetener without asking if that's what I wanted. They looked me in the face and told me that it wasn't sweet.......? My boyfriend and I both tasted it and it absolutely had sugar so I'm not sure why they were arguing with me about it, but I had to explain that I tasted it and it absolutely has sugar and I can't eat sugar. They didn't apologize or anything, just made another and silently handed it to me straight faced. No smiles, no "have a nice day", just surly employees who seemed annoyed that they had a customer. And these weren't teenagers but grown women. Very odd. Won't be returning, even though the coffee was good.
Our favorite place to get donuts as a family!
Great doughnuts
Wonderful donuts. Get there early for full selection of donuts. Never misses!!
Great service and a lot to choose from! Good coffee as well.

After finding this spot, there’s nowhere else in Charlotte I would go for donuts. The donuts have the perfect taste and texture and I’m usually reallllly picky about my donuts. I’ve yet to get a bad or even mediocre donut here. The coffee is delicious and everything is all reasonably priced.
Their donuts are nothing short of amazing. Some may say glazed are boring... they're my personal favorite.... then the chocolate iced. It's 7:30 pm and now I wish they were open.
OMG!

This morning was my first time going there ,after I was told this place was very good.  I didn't feel welcomed at all I started to turn around and leave but I was running late. The person behind the counter didn't greet me in fact he stood with his arms crossed in defensive mode. I said good morning he said how can I help you?  I asked any suggestions he asks as he didn't hear me. So I said glazed and a large black coffee and brown sugar flavor. He hands me a cup and says cream over there. He didn't tell me the coffee was there just rude. This white women comes in he greets her with a smile and  asked how was her morning. I said wow load for him to hear and I said I won't be back.  You get one chance to Impress me when it coms to speeding my money you need my service  I don't need your. I told my children not to return to this establishment.
Can’t say enough good things about OMG. Fantastic home made Donuts.
I took a bite and yes ... omg ! Great dounut! I had the buttermilk cake, and the blueberrie donut .

I am so glad I found out about this place from my daughter! They have the best donuts and it's always so good! And the workers and owners are always so welcoming! We try to make it on once a week for a donut for lunch! <3 we love it ! Won't be going to any other donut shop!
Everything is so yummy! People are so nice and the place is spotless!
The best apple fritters ever!!!
Got a dozen of the regular donuts. Amazing and fresh!
I just received my first order and let me tell you the donuts are amazing. Will definitely be going back
Awesome!
Their doughnuts are always delicious and fresh. The apple fritters are a family favorite.

Quick friendly service. The donutologist walked us through the process and explained the options. Great donuts and very tasty filling. We had chocolate cream filling in one and raspberry in another. Both were very good. The coffee was a bit small for the price, but everything else was on point.

Got donuts here for the first time today and loved it! The donuts are delicious and classic. I loved the fruity pebble donut, and my husband got one of the awesome filled-to-order glazed. The iced coffee was also great, and service was super friendly and fast. Can’t wait to come back!
I got them the other day for a meeting.  Someone bit into one then said...Oh my God. I said... that's why they are named exactly that! OMG
OMG THE APPLE FRITTER!!!  One of the best that I’ve ever had!  The staff was also as sweet as the product.  Perfect start to the morning!
The young dude who served me never even said a word to me. Rolled his eyes and nodded. Complete beta male.
Always delicious and nice staff. Highly recommend.
Best donuts we ever ordered! Fresh as can be and huge! Highly recommend!
Can't beat OMG!
Donuts are amazing. Customer service could improve.

OMG has a good thing going.  Donuts are delicious. Gotta try the carmel bacon donut and the buttermilk donut. The reason for not 5 stars is, for my taste, the donuts are too thick and not fluffy enough, and the icing is too sweet for me. I  am being very picky because, overall, they are good. Great place for kids, as we found out. Inside is very loud! Enjoy!

I don’t see this establishment being around much longer … Everytime I visit OMG Donuts  , I get a strong sense of the staff members being racist towards customers based on their race and ethnicity. It is unacceptable and disgusting that in this day and age, a place of business would harbor such discriminatory practices. Furthermore, the employees seem disinterested in serving customers. Their lack of enthusiasm and apathetic attitudes are palpable. You can tell they view us good-paying customers as an inconvenience, rather than the lifeblood of their business. I notice simple requests even from other customers were met with eye-rolls, sighs, and blatant disregard. Don’t spend your money in this place, it’s not worth being met with all of the negativity and rudeness and bad energy that comes from this place and family working there! The way they treat us good paying customers literally makes me want to see this business fail and I hope the store owner gets what he deserves!

Such a great environment with an amazing collection of donuts! Their cases were filled and I even got a little peak into the back in the kitchen where they were sprinkling sprinkles onto chocolate iced donuts.

I tried the Vietnamese coffee that comes with condensed milk that was very tasty. I came in around 8-9am and it wasn’t too packed but it looks like a great treat to do with the family or a fun date. I definitely want to come back and try some donuts and other drinks!

Long overdue, but we were there a couple months ago on a Sunday, stopping by the area with our toddler. Donuts were fantastic and my son fell off his chair and his donut fell with him... he was fine lol The shop owner/staff members were so sweet and replaced his donut even though he had eaten the top half aka icing portion of it. Would recommend the donuts and support them! Thank you!
Donuts are good. Size is good for price. Definitely recommend over most other places. Lots of selection, get there early
Sooooo goood
Excellent Apple fritter.  Definitely a super cheat food!  Fried but not greasy.  Almost tasted like those funnel cakes in a fair but better.
Strawberry shortcake
Nice and quiet donut shop. Great place to study. Even has a few small tables and chairs outside. They make a great dirty Chai latte.
Small joint, nice people, AMAZING donuts.
That apple fritter…OMG.
Excellent Apple Fritters and donuts!

These are the best donuts in Charlotte! Our favorite donut shop recently closed and decided to give this place a shot. All the flavors we tried were amazing and we can’t wait to come back and try the filled-to-order donuts. Vietnamese coffee was also a hit. A better price than other shops around and better quality.
The donuts are always fresh and delicious!
OMG! So soft and fluffy and perfect donuts! Will tell everyone and will return often.
Great donuts especially the Apple fritters!
Loved it!!! Doughnuts were EXCELLENT!!

I was absolutely blown away. After reading lots of reviews saying “best donuts in Charlotte”, I was a little skeptical but as soon as I bit into one - it was all over.

Hands down, these are the best donuts I’ve had in Charlotte. Absolutely delicious, light and fluffy, not overly sweet (even the maple glaze was still balanced and delicious), but the real winner for me is the buttermilk crumb cake donut.

Holy cow. Definitely coming back ASAP.

Great donuts!
If you don't think these donuts are awesome then you just don't like donuts.
The best donuts in North Carolina hands down.

Although their donuts run out very quick, there are still several to choose from. Also donuts are worth the price & the right size (unlike dunkin). I love the brownie donuts so much those are the best!!!
Their donuts are fresh and delicious. Sometimes the filling isn't quite enough when I ask for extra filling. The cinnamon donuts are the best. Staff is very friendly.
The absolute best traditional donuts I've had in Charlotte.  Every one is perfect.  Chocolate frosting is superb.  The vanilla and Bavarian cream fillings are excellent.

Hands down the best donuts in Charlotte area. These truly are specialty donuts.  I have visited on and off for several years and they are consistently good. Occasionally they feel heavy with oil ( not sure if some batches have over used oil), but they are always good. Crushes "your mom's donuts" ( and half the price), and much better than cake like donuts at "Duck Donuts".
Delicious.
The donuts is scrumptious. The service was great
Great donuts, great people!

The donuts are freaking amazing. I've never seen another shop fill donuts to order like this! They run out hours before closing and just close early, so hopefully they'll figure out how to fix that issue soon.

Just stuck with a classic glazed and a latte. Nice atmosphere,  friendly staff. They were doing a fairly brisk business with a number of small families popping in to keep the kiddos jazzed up on sugar and themselves on caffeine.
Delicious donuts! Light and fluffy. Very fresh. Friendly service. Affordable prices. So far, it’s our favorite donut shop in the Charlotte area!
Highly recommended
They have the best donuts!!! 🍩 staff is super nice!
Wow, their glazed donuts are easily the best in Charlotte, and there is a lot of competition. The secret that locals know is that OMG is much better than the Starbucks down the street.
Pleasant service, fresh and delicious donuts.
So so good! I got there around 11am on a Sunday and they were sold out except for glazed. Wasn’t expecting much from a simple glazed doughnut but omg! Go early. Worth the drive.
The donuts are amazing but every time I stop by in the morning their closed! 🥺
dare I say better than Krispy Kreme?
Such a tasty selection! The donuts and coffee are so cheap for such great stuff. Took these to work and got rave reviews!
Great donuts and good coffee too!
Best doughnuts in town.
The donuts are amazing!! They are tasty and a great price. And I had the iced coffee - so refreshing! You have to check this place out - good location as well!

Really excited they have opened a second location! If you want mom and pop doughnuts this is your spot! The doughnuts are always top notch and fresh. My go to is an iced Vietnamese coffee, and a maple bacon glazed donut. You also have the ability to choose donuts in which filling you would like. So you can get really creative!
OMG donuts is the best place to get donuts doughnuts made fresh daily.
The donuts here are delicious and the location is decent. This is our go-to spot to satisfy that donut itch!

My husband, 2 kids and I LOVE LOVE LOVE their donuts. We have only been to the Monroe Rd location so I can't speak to the other locations. Staff is friendly, service is quick. Their donuts are fluffy, flavorful, and always fresh. I would have a hard time enjoying donuts from somewhere else bc OMG Donuts have raised the bar ❤️ I was not a fan of the mocha coffee that I got but my husband loved his chai. Would absolutely recommend this place! You won't want donuts from anywhere else!
They have my favorite donut .. Maple Glazed! Such a nice and clean shop .. the Donuts are delicious and they are really nice !
OMG you open a franchise of this amazing doughnut shop and can't open for business more than weekend hours?!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Apologies, we are open on weekdays but sometimes, we do run out of donuts before actual closing time.  Today we sold out a little before 4pm.

The weekend hours posted are just our temporary hours for weekends operation.

reviews_data.review_text: Love my local donut shop never disappointed.The Apple fritters are to Die for

One of my favorite people in the whole world introduced me to MJ Donuts years ago. It's still the best! Try the apple fritter. Open til 4pm or 5pm everyday (except it's closed on Mondays). The outside of the building hides how wonderful all the Treasures are inside the store.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review Cathy, but we're OMG Donuts.  ;)

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious apple fritter and good Pure Intentions coffee.
So quite and quaint. Great choices too!
Very tasty and fresh, a great donut place! You can even choose your creme filling!

I really have to be careful when I come here or I’ll pack on pounds. Their doughnuts are too damn good and they’re filling. Krispy Kreme used to be my favorite, but now they have been replace. Hands down the best doughnuts I’ve ever had.

The shop certainly lives up to it's name! OMG is exactly what I would have said if I would have paused long enough while enjoying the fresh, soft, delicious cinnamon bun that I had. We were so impressed, we purchased two dozen different types that they offered for some students at the high school nearby, to enjoy before their musical later that day. OMG, please go and get yourself some of their delicious, decadent delicacies!!
Great local spot for doughnuts that are tasty and fresh. Polite and friendly staff too.
Reminds me of status dough in Knoxville. Very fresh

Believe the hype! OMG's donuts will keep you coming back again and again. Mia perfectly balances a soft, but substantial donut that's perfectly sweet (not cloying). The apple fritter is in a class by itself. Don't pass it up. They're definitely baking something special over there on Monroe Road.
The bomb!
OMG is right! Donuts warm and fresh all day! The maple bacon was soft like a cloud, the strawberry with sprinkles melted in my mouth, and the coffee was STRONG. Can’t praise this place enough!

Stopped here on 11/12/2021 and wow what a wonderful place this is! They have all different types of doughnuts and you can choose your fillings too.  I’ve had them before and they were delicious so I wanted to go and try them again so I could do a review!  The staff was also very friendly!  I’ll let the photos do the talking!!!

Thank me later!
Absolutely love this place, the donuts are amazing, the customer service is amazing m. Definitely recommend this place
Awesome!!!
Best donuts I’ve had in the Charlotte area! Service is friendly, prices are great and they have coffee options as well! The cookies and cream donut was AMAZING.
Love their donuts!
Very good donuts but a little pricey. Glad to finally find a place near me, who wants to drive to House of Donuts in Matthew's for treat. Way better than Krispy or Dunkin. Definitely worth a try
Bought 2 dozen for an account.  They raved about them.

The cinnamon/sugar donut was so good and soft. I’m just upset that it was the last one, I went in at 4:50. But guess who will be there tomorrow to buy another. Meee!!!! And being my first time there they were willing to tell me what was what lol. Thanks
Son las mejores aquí en North Carolina awww me encantan

I have lived from Los Angeles to San Diego in California, Texas, Oklahoma, Puerto Rico, Louisiana, and now Charlotte. AND I'M OLD!!

These are hands down the best donuts I have ever had!!!!!!!!!!!!

You can't do better.

First time there after after a colleague of mine recommended It… love!!! Very relaxing atmosphere and the employees were very sweet and accommodating… will be back for sure! Donuts are the best I’ve had in awhile, better than Krispy Kreme to me

Quality of the donuts were amazing and the ladies who attended me were very friendly. Super nice environment and I’m definitely coming back for seconds!

10/10

OMG is such a great place! I first fell in love with the donuts in Concord. They really are set apart from the other donut shops here.

Very clean business serving fresh donuts, coffee and more; with excellent customer service as well. Having the location within walking distance may be a little dangerous😁

LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS PLACE. I’m not really a donut person but I do enjoy their cake donuts. I had the seasonal one and it was buttermilk flavor and it was just too good. If you don’t really like donuts like me then I would suggest trying a cake donut. But I do love coffee and this place makes the BEST coffee ever! Even better than Starbucks might I add. I love their iced latte with caramel and also their iced mocha as well. If you have sensitivity to milk then I would suggest trying it with oatmilk because it’s so delicious!! I especially love the mocha with oatmilk because it taste so good and they make it to where you can barely taste the milk. Overall this place is amazing and I think everyone should try this place!

Man, man, man! This about to be my favorite place! OMG Donuts & Coffee is the perfect name for this place, because after my first bite of that big fluffy donut ( that melted in my mouth. Lol) that was all I could say! The coffee was everything! The prices low, that's always a good thing! I'm gonna try not to go everyday, but I already know I'm gonna be there a lot. Lol...so come check them out! If you see me there don't judge me. Lol... just say hey and grab a donut and some coffee!!
Delicious
So good and great customer service!!!!
The friendliest people work here and the donuts are the best I have had the bacon donut 🍩 is my favorite
I've been on the hunt for true southern California style donuts in the Queen City for years. I finally found them here. These are the best donuts in Charlotte. Full stop.
Best apple fritter I've ever had. I don't have a picture of it... because I ate it. 😋
Like a "make your own donut" bar. My new favorite. You can mix can match shells and fills. This is a concept long overdue and the quality is absolutely tip notch.

Delicious donuts. Great coffee. Friendly service. Clean establishment and outdoor seating. Donuts are big and soft, fresh tasting and not overly sweet. This is my second time and I can tell this will be a regular spot for us!

Wow, we have loved having this so close by. Fantastic donuts at a really good price with wide selection to keep everyone happy. The blueberry frosted and cookies & cream have been my favorites thus far but everything I have tried has been good. Great coffee as well! We will be back (regularly)

OMG these are the best donuts I have ever had! So big, so fluffy and extremely fresh. I love the pick your own filling. I got one filled with Raspberry and I got a smores specialty donut. The marshmallows on top were actually toasted.. perfection. They have coffee and ice cream too. We need one in Raleigh! I will definitely come here every single time I'm nearby.. or far away, it's that good. Definitely worth a drive.
Our new go to donut shop.  Incredibly soft and pillowy, and not overly sweet or over the top with too much toppings.  Doesn't break the bank earthier.

Super excited to see OMG Donuts opened up in the Monroe Rd area! We tried OMG Donuts this past weekend and loved it. The donuts tasted so fresh and were very fluffy. We did a dozen and got a good variety to see how it was and loved it. Excellent customer service, great donuts and the building is super nice and spacious along with outside seating. Highly recommend giving OMG Donuts a try. Will definitely return back for more!

Had to check out OMG Donuts & Coffee. So glad I did. They had an amazing selection of different types of donuts. I went with the s’mores, strawberry and the buttermilk cake donut. All were super fresh and absolutely delicious. They had a ton of different flavors to choose from and coffee too! I wish I bought more so I’ll have to go back!!!
Great donuts, and great coffee, will be back!

Their donuts are amazing. We ordered a half dozen and were impressed with the price and overall quality of the donuts. I enjoyed the blueberry frosted and chocolate frosted donuts most. My husband enjoyed the cookies and cream donut. Coffee was really good as well and inexpensive for a large size. So glad they are in the neighborhood!

popular_times.title: Usually as busy as it gets
Usually as busy as it gets
Usually as busy as it gets

reviews_data.review_text: Best blueberry donuts ever! A must try.
Lots of good baked items
Their donuts are so fresh and fluffy every time. They have great flavors and the staff are always super nice and friendly. Will continue to come back! Support a local business!
Sunday morning, about 10am, no one else there...friendly service, great selection. The apple fritter is very good.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Doughnut, Apple Fritter, Blueberry Glazed Donut

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome and amazing donuts! At first I thought they only had donuts which are out of this world amazing but then I also saw that they had all types of coffee and tea! Everything was wonderful! I got a coffee and a Vietnamese coffee there’s a lot of selections that are so good!!! We go to the Lamborghini events that get a bunch of these donuts and hand them out and I see why. Good customer service too, the lady’s were sweet! Overall my most favorite donuts in Charlotte!
Best donuts in Charlotte by far!!!
No idea because they're never opened when I attempt to go. Always "ran out of donuts" sign on the door.
Get donuts! They do sell out, sometimes around noon.
Went for the first time this morning. Bye 👋 Starbucks lol. I have found my spot.
The best donuts in the Charlotte metro area.  I love their apple fritter donuts. When you order a filled donut they fill it while you wait. Their donuts are always fresh and very soft.

We love the donuts, the different options for fillings and the apple fritters. Unfortunately, we are really disappointed to see that they are closing at 3 now. We love to stop by for an after school snack and if they close at 3 we can’t ever make it. Every time we would go in there we would run into other kids just getting out of school so I don’t know why they would choose to lose all that business. We will never be able to go anymore.
Cool

Awful service! I have purchased donuts from here before and they weren't bad like the service that I received but my family and I will NEVER spend any of our hard earned money here again and neither should you!

Saw this donut shop on our way to Great Wolf Lodge and I after Googling it I knew I had to stop on our way home. BOY OH BOY was it worth the stop. We went around 1pm but there was still a lot of variety of options left. These donuts were SOOOOOOO good! Trying to talk myself out of driving back to Charlotte to get some more!
Definitely a must have!
The BEST donuts!
Doughnuts are always fresh.
Best donuts in town. Donut holes are a must to snack on. Love this place. Amazing selection. Friendly service.  Delicious coffee. Cute inside with places to sit and eat.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Doughnut, Apple Fritter, Cake Donut, Maple Bacon, Buttermilk Cake Crumble Donut, Cinnamon Roll, Chocolate Glazed Donut with Sprinkles, Smores Doughnut Top Left, Blueberry Cake Donut, Cinnamon Sugar, Chocolate Coconut, Salted Caramel, Cinnamon Sugar Holes

reviews_data.review_text: My favorite thing to do in a city is to try their donuts. I checked a few and wasn’t impressed and then stumbled across Omg Donuts. There donuts were massive, colorful and delicious. My favorite feature was the select your own filling station ( Bavarian, white crème, raspberry and lemon). The staff was super friendly. I understand why they are rated so highly. I will definitely come back

This is a solid, all-around good place.   I had the lemon doughnut, and it was flavorful.  The service was friendly.   They warmed up the doughnut, which I believe made it so much better, and the place has a cute ambiance. It is tucked away a bit but appears to be a nice place to sit down and enjoy coffee in doughnuts, whether you're hanging out with family and friends,  on a date, or needing a quiet place to work and study as well.
These donuts are amazingly delicious. Me and the kids got a cinnamon roll, an apple fritter, and a frosted donut. I think they were the best I’ve ever had. Highly recommend if you were in the area.
Donuts are phenomenally fresh and they have amazing taste and texture. They remind me of my childhood donuts.  Absolutely, irresistible donuts!
Donuts where so soft and fluffy not to sweet they where pretty good, it would have been nice to have a little more variety, but again I have to say, they do what they do well.
Delicious…. Every time! OMG for the win!
One of the best chocolate long johns and cinnamon roll I have ever had. The staff were very friendly as well.
One of my favorites.
Loved the donuts, they are made fresh daily.
Drove from ohio.. been wanting these since I saw them 3 yrs ago.. gas 500 hotel 800 OMG DONUTS PRICELESS
Food. Service. Atmosphere. All 5/5!!! The donuts are perfectly fluffy, great size, and tasty flavors. Plus they are an amazing value for the price! My new go to spot!

Absolutely the best donut shop!!! Super friendly excellent customer service absolutely wonderful donuts and wonderful Vietnamese iced coffee. I have been to the shop many many times The donuts are consistently pillowy soft and the service is wonderful they're always happy to see you and happy to help and answer any questions you have. And I love that when I want a filled donut, I can choose my filling and they fill it right there on the spot everything is super fresh.
Absolutely delicious! Massive donuts, great selection. Two really kind ladies working. Will definitely return

A true disappointment!   I’ve seen a better selection at Dunkin Donuts.   The staff doesn’t even greet you when you walk in.   It was a no brainer to leave immediately.  I will not return.  OMG what a disappointment!

Other than some pretty good donuts, this is the most untrustworthy, and unreliable donut shop ever. Never open when they say they are with no signs or updates. The door at the front doesn’t even have their hours because they close and open whenever they feel like. This place is a guessing game and frankly, I’m not having fun. Highly suggest going somewhere else. There’s better donuts anyway.
The most amazing donuts in the area

Incredibly fresh and well-made donuts. Complex in flavor and great chew. You can pick your donut fillings, and there's even Bavarian cream! The people who work here are always a joy to talk to and I can't wait to go back.
First time coming here and it was amazing! donuts were so good and CHEAP! had to buy more! will for sure come back!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Apple Fritter, Cake Donut, Blueberry Glazed Donut

reviews_data.review_text: Best donut in town.  I have the maple bacon donut and maple bar quite often.  Very good.

The worst customer service I have ever experienced. The cashier couldn’t even initiate ordering or telling us what order was ours. It was the most bizarre experience like she couldn’t be bothered to do her job.
Great donuts, rating a 4 because they don’t have decaf coffee. Never been to a coffee shop that doesn’t have decaf.

We usually go to the Concord location but finally tried this location. The donuts were amazing as usual but I could’ve dealt without the young light skinned girls stale attitude that checked us out. She lacks all sense of any type of customer service. She felt very cold and uninviting. Other than that, the donuts are always great.
I enjoyed the treats I got here. I got some donut holes and a lemon filled and a creme filled donut. Looking forward to coming back

Read in entirety:
Just want to thank Krispy Kreme for no longer carrying blueberry cake donuts because it made me search for another donut shop. And as the clouds part and angels sing, we have found it!!  OMG Donuts !  The blueberry cake donut was very bluebery-eee and the lightest cake donut I have had.  But the best one (so far...) is their apple fritter donut.  It is THE BEST APPLE FRITTER DONUT EVER CREATED!
Now, on to try the creme filled donuts...(did you know you get to pick your filling and what kind of donut it goes into and they fill it right there?! I mean, COME ON!)

YES YES YES!!!... FRESH FRESH FRESH!!! The donuts are just so delicious, soft, and flavorful. You can tell they're fresh EVERYTIME. They even have different filling options that they fill right infront of you, FRESH!.
Take out order!

Just came from here, to pick up some donuts. Man, could the service be *anymore* underwhelming? One girl was handling the donuts, and another rang us up. Now SHE looked absolutely *thrilled* to be there. I could barely even hear what she said about how much I owed her because she barely moved her mouth. VERY lackluster, and could’ve cared less. And they have the audacity to ask for a tip??? That's hilarious. All around, it was a very awkward interaction. If I wanted service like that, I should've just gone to Dunkin or Krispy Kreme. They don't care either. Listen, if you guys want to stand out from the typical chains, hire people with a personality and TRAIN them on customer service!!! 3-stars for the donuts, but that's about it. It'll be a while before I go back. It’s enough to keep me away.
Best donuts for the price in Charlotte. $1.50-$2 for almost every donut while other places are charging 2x that! Give this place a visit, you will have a new fav donut spot too.

OMG is consistently delicious whenever we visit. I love the lemon doughnut and coffee and my husbands favorite is the Apple fritter. Actually, our entire family loves OMG as well. So much so we decided to have OMG at our wedding.  Our guests kept commenting how delicious everything was.

Highly recommend OMG for daily treats and large orders for events!

(Wedding Photography by: Jamie Marie Photography)
Came for coffee and left with an apple fritter and filled to order eclair (for wife). Wow. Best donuts I ever had. So fresh and crisp. Coffee was great too.
I don’t ever review anything but these are the best donuts in Charlotte hands down…
The best donuts I ever had!
Best donuts, hands down. A great selection and the apple fritters are a must have!!!
Best glazed yeast donuts. Ever.
Everyone was quick and friendly, donuts tasted great.

Love this place!  My kids and I wanted to surprise their Mom on Mother’s Day, as she is a NICU nurse & had to work. She & her co- workers loved the dozen doughnuts we brought in. The staff were super helpful/kind picking out her favorite doughnuts/chatting with me & the price was much cheaper than I thought it would be. My kids loved the doughnuts they picked for themselves & the restaurant itself was set up very nicely. Go OMG!

The coffee was good but the customer service was terrible. Both employees were very rude when I politely asked them to remake my coffee because they added sweetener without asking if that's what I wanted. They looked me in the face and told me that it wasn't sweet.......? My boyfriend and I both tasted it and it absolutely had sugar so I'm not sure why they were arguing with me about it, but I had to explain that I tasted it and it absolutely has sugar and I can't eat sugar. They didn't apologize or anything, just made another and silently handed it to me straight faced. No smiles, no "have a nice day", just surly employees who seemed annoyed that they had a customer. And these weren't teenagers but grown women. Very odd. Won't be returning, even though the coffee was good.
Our favorite place to get donuts as a family!
Great doughnuts
Wonderful donuts. Get there early for full selection of donuts. Never misses!!
Great service and a lot to choose from! Good coffee as well.

After finding this spot, there’s nowhere else in Charlotte I would go for donuts. The donuts have the perfect taste and texture and I’m usually reallllly picky about my donuts. I’ve yet to get a bad or even mediocre donut here. The coffee is delicious and everything is all reasonably priced.
Their donuts are nothing short of amazing. Some may say glazed are boring... they're my personal favorite.... then the chocolate iced. It's 7:30 pm and now I wish they were open.
OMG!

This morning was my first time going there ,after I was told this place was very good.  I didn't feel welcomed at all I started to turn around and leave but I was running late. The person behind the counter didn't greet me in fact he stood with his arms crossed in defensive mode. I said good morning he said how can I help you?  I asked any suggestions he asks as he didn't hear me. So I said glazed and a large black coffee and brown sugar flavor. He hands me a cup and says cream over there. He didn't tell me the coffee was there just rude. This white women comes in he greets her with a smile and  asked how was her morning. I said wow load for him to hear and I said I won't be back.  You get one chance to Impress me when it coms to speeding my money you need my service  I don't need your. I told my children not to return to this establishment.
Can’t say enough good things about OMG. Fantastic home made Donuts.
I took a bite and yes ... omg ! Great dounut! I had the buttermilk cake, and the blueberrie donut .

I am so glad I found out about this place from my daughter! They have the best donuts and it's always so good! And the workers and owners are always so welcoming! We try to make it on once a week for a donut for lunch! <3 we love it ! Won't be going to any other donut shop!
Everything is so yummy! People are so nice and the place is spotless!
The best apple fritters ever!!!
Got a dozen of the regular donuts. Amazing and fresh!
I just received my first order and let me tell you the donuts are amazing. Will definitely be going back
Awesome!
Their doughnuts are always delicious and fresh. The apple fritters are a family favorite.

Quick friendly service. The donutologist walked us through the process and explained the options. Great donuts and very tasty filling. We had chocolate cream filling in one and raspberry in another. Both were very good. The coffee was a bit small for the price, but everything else was on point.

Got donuts here for the first time today and loved it! The donuts are delicious and classic. I loved the fruity pebble donut, and my husband got one of the awesome filled-to-order glazed. The iced coffee was also great, and service was super friendly and fast. Can’t wait to come back!
I got them the other day for a meeting.  Someone bit into one then said...Oh my God. I said... that's why they are named exactly that! OMG
OMG THE APPLE FRITTER!!!  One of the best that I’ve ever had!  The staff was also as sweet as the product.  Perfect start to the morning!
The young dude who served me never even said a word to me. Rolled his eyes and nodded. Complete beta male.
Always delicious and nice staff. Highly recommend.
Best donuts we ever ordered! Fresh as can be and huge! Highly recommend!
Can't beat OMG!
Donuts are amazing. Customer service could improve.

OMG has a good thing going.  Donuts are delicious. Gotta try the carmel bacon donut and the buttermilk donut. The reason for not 5 stars is, for my taste, the donuts are too thick and not fluffy enough, and the icing is too sweet for me. I  am being very picky because, overall, they are good. Great place for kids, as we found out. Inside is very loud! Enjoy!

I don’t see this establishment being around much longer … Everytime I visit OMG Donuts  , I get a strong sense of the staff members being racist towards customers based on their race and ethnicity. It is unacceptable and disgusting that in this day and age, a place of business would harbor such discriminatory practices. Furthermore, the employees seem disinterested in serving customers. Their lack of enthusiasm and apathetic attitudes are palpable. You can tell they view us good-paying customers as an inconvenience, rather than the lifeblood of their business. I notice simple requests even from other customers were met with eye-rolls, sighs, and blatant disregard. Don’t spend your money in this place, it’s not worth being met with all of the negativity and rudeness and bad energy that comes from this place and family working there! The way they treat us good paying customers literally makes me want to see this business fail and I hope the store owner gets what he deserves!

Such a great environment with an amazing collection of donuts! Their cases were filled and I even got a little peak into the back in the kitchen where they were sprinkling sprinkles onto chocolate iced donuts.

I tried the Vietnamese coffee that comes with condensed milk that was very tasty. I came in around 8-9am and it wasn’t too packed but it looks like a great treat to do with the family or a fun date. I definitely want to come back and try some donuts and other drinks!

Long overdue, but we were there a couple months ago on a Sunday, stopping by the area with our toddler. Donuts were fantastic and my son fell off his chair and his donut fell with him... he was fine lol The shop owner/staff members were so sweet and replaced his donut even though he had eaten the top half aka icing portion of it. Would recommend the donuts and support them! Thank you!
Donuts are good. Size is good for price. Definitely recommend over most other places. Lots of selection, get there early
Sooooo goood
Excellent Apple fritter.  Definitely a super cheat food!  Fried but not greasy.  Almost tasted like those funnel cakes in a fair but better.
Strawberry shortcake
Nice and quiet donut shop. Great place to study. Even has a few small tables and chairs outside. They make a great dirty Chai latte.
Small joint, nice people, AMAZING donuts.
That apple fritter…OMG.
Excellent Apple Fritters and donuts!

These are the best donuts in Charlotte! Our favorite donut shop recently closed and decided to give this place a shot. All the flavors we tried were amazing and we can’t wait to come back and try the filled-to-order donuts. Vietnamese coffee was also a hit. A better price than other shops around and better quality.
The donuts are always fresh and delicious!
OMG! So soft and fluffy and perfect donuts! Will tell everyone and will return often.
Great donuts especially the Apple fritters!
Loved it!!! Doughnuts were EXCELLENT!!

I was absolutely blown away. After reading lots of reviews saying “best donuts in Charlotte”, I was a little skeptical but as soon as I bit into one - it was all over.

Hands down, these are the best donuts I’ve had in Charlotte. Absolutely delicious, light and fluffy, not overly sweet (even the maple glaze was still balanced and delicious), but the real winner for me is the buttermilk crumb cake donut.

Holy cow. Definitely coming back ASAP.

Great donuts!
If you don't think these donuts are awesome then you just don't like donuts.
The best donuts in North Carolina hands down.

Although their donuts run out very quick, there are still several to choose from. Also donuts are worth the price & the right size (unlike dunkin). I love the brownie donuts so much those are the best!!!
Their donuts are fresh and delicious. Sometimes the filling isn't quite enough when I ask for extra filling. The cinnamon donuts are the best. Staff is very friendly.
The absolute best traditional donuts I've had in Charlotte.  Every one is perfect.  Chocolate frosting is superb.  The vanilla and Bavarian cream fillings are excellent.

Hands down the best donuts in Charlotte area. These truly are specialty donuts.  I have visited on and off for several years and they are consistently good. Occasionally they feel heavy with oil ( not sure if some batches have over used oil), but they are always good. Crushes "your mom's donuts" ( and half the price), and much better than cake like donuts at "Duck Donuts".
Delicious.
The donuts is scrumptious. The service was great
Great donuts, great people!

The donuts are freaking amazing. I've never seen another shop fill donuts to order like this! They run out hours before closing and just close early, so hopefully they'll figure out how to fix that issue soon.

Just stuck with a classic glazed and a latte. Nice atmosphere,  friendly staff. They were doing a fairly brisk business with a number of small families popping in to keep the kiddos jazzed up on sugar and themselves on caffeine.
Delicious donuts! Light and fluffy. Very fresh. Friendly service. Affordable prices. So far, it’s our favorite donut shop in the Charlotte area!
Highly recommended
They have the best donuts!!! 🍩 staff is super nice!
Wow, their glazed donuts are easily the best in Charlotte, and there is a lot of competition. The secret that locals know is that OMG is much better than the Starbucks down the street.
Pleasant service, fresh and delicious donuts.
So so good! I got there around 11am on a Sunday and they were sold out except for glazed. Wasn’t expecting much from a simple glazed doughnut but omg! Go early. Worth the drive.
The donuts are amazing but every time I stop by in the morning their closed! 🥺
dare I say better than Krispy Kreme?
Such a tasty selection! The donuts and coffee are so cheap for such great stuff. Took these to work and got rave reviews!
Great donuts and good coffee too!
Best doughnuts in town.
The donuts are amazing!! They are tasty and a great price. And I had the iced coffee - so refreshing! You have to check this place out - good location as well!

Really excited they have opened a second location! If you want mom and pop doughnuts this is your spot! The doughnuts are always top notch and fresh. My go to is an iced Vietnamese coffee, and a maple bacon glazed donut. You also have the ability to choose donuts in which filling you would like. So you can get really creative!
OMG donuts is the best place to get donuts doughnuts made fresh daily.
The donuts here are delicious and the location is decent. This is our go-to spot to satisfy that donut itch!

My husband, 2 kids and I LOVE LOVE LOVE their donuts. We have only been to the Monroe Rd location so I can't speak to the other locations. Staff is friendly, service is quick. Their donuts are fluffy, flavorful, and always fresh. I would have a hard time enjoying donuts from somewhere else bc OMG Donuts have raised the bar ❤️ I was not a fan of the mocha coffee that I got but my husband loved his chai. Would absolutely recommend this place! You won't want donuts from anywhere else!
They have my favorite donut .. Maple Glazed! Such a nice and clean shop .. the Donuts are delicious and they are really nice !
OMG you open a franchise of this amazing doughnut shop and can't open for business more than weekend hours?!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Apologies, we are open on weekdays but sometimes, we do run out of donuts before actual closing time.  Today we sold out a little before 4pm.

The weekend hours posted are just our temporary hours for weekends operation.

reviews_data.review_text: Love my local donut shop never disappointed.The Apple fritters are to Die for

One of my favorite people in the whole world introduced me to MJ Donuts years ago. It's still the best! Try the apple fritter. Open til 4pm or 5pm everyday (except it's closed on Mondays). The outside of the building hides how wonderful all the Treasures are inside the store.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review Cathy, but we're OMG Donuts.  ;)

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious apple fritter and good Pure Intentions coffee.
So quite and quaint. Great choices too!
Very tasty and fresh, a great donut place! You can even choose your creme filling!

I really have to be careful when I come here or I’ll pack on pounds. Their doughnuts are too damn good and they’re filling. Krispy Kreme used to be my favorite, but now they have been replace. Hands down the best doughnuts I’ve ever had.

The shop certainly lives up to it's name! OMG is exactly what I would have said if I would have paused long enough while enjoying the fresh, soft, delicious cinnamon bun that I had. We were so impressed, we purchased two dozen different types that they offered for some students at the high school nearby, to enjoy before their musical later that day. OMG, please go and get yourself some of their delicious, decadent delicacies!!
Great local spot for doughnuts that are tasty and fresh. Polite and friendly staff too.
Reminds me of status dough in Knoxville. Very fresh

Believe the hype! OMG's donuts will keep you coming back again and again. Mia perfectly balances a soft, but substantial donut that's perfectly sweet (not cloying). The apple fritter is in a class by itself. Don't pass it up. They're definitely baking something special over there on Monroe Road.
The bomb!
OMG is right! Donuts warm and fresh all day! The maple bacon was soft like a cloud, the strawberry with sprinkles melted in my mouth, and the coffee was STRONG. Can’t praise this place enough!

Stopped here on 11/12/2021 and wow what a wonderful place this is! They have all different types of doughnuts and you can choose your fillings too.  I’ve had them before and they were delicious so I wanted to go and try them again so I could do a review!  The staff was also very friendly!  I’ll let the photos do the talking!!!

Thank me later!
Absolutely love this place, the donuts are amazing, the customer service is amazing m. Definitely recommend this place
Awesome!!!
Best donuts I’ve had in the Charlotte area! Service is friendly, prices are great and they have coffee options as well! The cookies and cream donut was AMAZING.
Love their donuts!
Very good donuts but a little pricey. Glad to finally find a place near me, who wants to drive to House of Donuts in Matthew's for treat. Way better than Krispy or Dunkin. Definitely worth a try
Bought 2 dozen for an account.  They raved about them.

The cinnamon/sugar donut was so good and soft. I’m just upset that it was the last one, I went in at 4:50. But guess who will be there tomorrow to buy another. Meee!!!! And being my first time there they were willing to tell me what was what lol. Thanks
Son las mejores aquí en North Carolina awww me encantan

I have lived from Los Angeles to San Diego in California, Texas, Oklahoma, Puerto Rico, Louisiana, and now Charlotte. AND I'M OLD!!

These are hands down the best donuts I have ever had!!!!!!!!!!!!

You can't do better.

First time there after after a colleague of mine recommended It… love!!! Very relaxing atmosphere and the employees were very sweet and accommodating… will be back for sure! Donuts are the best I’ve had in awhile, better than Krispy Kreme to me

Quality of the donuts were amazing and the ladies who attended me were very friendly. Super nice environment and I’m definitely coming back for seconds!

10/10

OMG is such a great place! I first fell in love with the donuts in Concord. They really are set apart from the other donut shops here.

Very clean business serving fresh donuts, coffee and more; with excellent customer service as well. Having the location within walking distance may be a little dangerous😁

LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS PLACE. I’m not really a donut person but I do enjoy their cake donuts. I had the seasonal one and it was buttermilk flavor and it was just too good. If you don’t really like donuts like me then I would suggest trying a cake donut. But I do love coffee and this place makes the BEST coffee ever! Even better than Starbucks might I add. I love their iced latte with caramel and also their iced mocha as well. If you have sensitivity to milk then I would suggest trying it with oatmilk because it’s so delicious!! I especially love the mocha with oatmilk because it taste so good and they make it to where you can barely taste the milk. Overall this place is amazing and I think everyone should try this place!

Man, man, man! This about to be my favorite place! OMG Donuts & Coffee is the perfect name for this place, because after my first bite of that big fluffy donut ( that melted in my mouth. Lol) that was all I could say! The coffee was everything! The prices low, that's always a good thing! I'm gonna try not to go everyday, but I already know I'm gonna be there a lot. Lol...so come check them out! If you see me there don't judge me. Lol... just say hey and grab a donut and some coffee!!
Delicious
So good and great customer service!!!!
The friendliest people work here and the donuts are the best I have had the bacon donut 🍩 is my favorite
I've been on the hunt for true southern California style donuts in the Queen City for years. I finally found them here. These are the best donuts in Charlotte. Full stop.
Best apple fritter I've ever had. I don't have a picture of it... because I ate it. 😋
Like a "make your own donut" bar. My new favorite. You can mix can match shells and fills. This is a concept long overdue and the quality is absolutely tip notch.

Delicious donuts. Great coffee. Friendly service. Clean establishment and outdoor seating. Donuts are big and soft, fresh tasting and not overly sweet. This is my second time and I can tell this will be a regular spot for us!

Wow, we have loved having this so close by. Fantastic donuts at a really good price with wide selection to keep everyone happy. The blueberry frosted and cookies & cream have been my favorites thus far but everything I have tried has been good. Great coffee as well! We will be back (regularly)

OMG these are the best donuts I have ever had! So big, so fluffy and extremely fresh. I love the pick your own filling. I got one filled with Raspberry and I got a smores specialty donut. The marshmallows on top were actually toasted.. perfection. They have coffee and ice cream too. We need one in Raleigh! I will definitely come here every single time I'm nearby.. or far away, it's that good. Definitely worth a drive.
Our new go to donut shop.  Incredibly soft and pillowy, and not overly sweet or over the top with too much toppings.  Doesn't break the bank earthier.

Super excited to see OMG Donuts opened up in the Monroe Rd area! We tried OMG Donuts this past weekend and loved it. The donuts tasted so fresh and were very fluffy. We did a dozen and got a good variety to see how it was and loved it. Excellent customer service, great donuts and the building is super nice and spacious along with outside seating. Highly recommend giving OMG Donuts a try. Will definitely return back for more!

Had to check out OMG Donuts & Coffee. So glad I did. They had an amazing selection of different types of donuts. I went with the s’mores, strawberry and the buttermilk cake donut. All were super fresh and absolutely delicious. They had a ton of different flavors to choose from and coffee too! I wish I bought more so I’ll have to go back!!!
Great donuts, and great coffee, will be back!

Their donuts are amazing. We ordered a half dozen and were impressed with the price and overall quality of the donuts. I enjoyed the blueberry frosted and chocolate frosted donuts most. My husband enjoyed the cookies and cream donut. Coffee was really good as well and inexpensive for a large size. So glad they are in the neighborhood!
